President Cyril Ramaphosa will meet with the National
Education, Health and Allied Workers Union (NEHAWU) on Friday. The meeting follows the union’s submission of a memorandum
to the President on improving occupational health and safety regularly in connection
to the COVID-19 pandemic, and wages. Minister for the Public Service and Administration Senzo
Mchunu and Deputy Minister of Health Dr Joe Phaahla will also be part of the
meeting which will be held at the President’s official residence, Mahlamba
Ndlopfu, in Pretoria. 